        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 3:44PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 344 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hartford, or 12 miles south of Whitehall, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hudson Falls, Whitehall, Arlington, Salem, Manchester, Fort Edward,
Granville, Hartford, Dorset, Greenwich, Comstock, Manchester Center,
Poultney Village, Gates, Kingsbury, Porter, Northumberland,
Schuylerville, Sunderland, and Hampton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
